  "title": "Kinetic energy of a projectile to escape planet",
  "content": {
    "description": "",
    "question": "Let g be the acceleration due to gravity at the surface of a planet of radius R. Which of the following is a dimensionally correct formula for the minimum kinetic energy K that a projectile of mass m must have at the planet’s surface if the projectile is to escape from the planet’s gravitational field?",
    "image": null,
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "K = <math> <semantics> <mrow> <msqrt> <mrow> <mi>g</mi><mi>R</mi> </mrow> </msqrt> </mrow> <annotation encoding=\"MathType-MTEF\">MathType@MTEF@5@5@@3811@</annotation> </semantics> </math>",
        "image": null
      },
      {
        "label": "K = mgR",
        "image": null
      },
      {
        "label": "K = <math> <semantics> <mrow> <mfrac> <mrow> <mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi> </mrow> <mi>R</mi> </mfrac> </mrow> <annotation encoding=\"MathType-MTEF\">MathType@MTEF@5@5@@3917@</annotation> </semantics> </math>",
        "image": null
      },
      {
        "label": "K = <math> <semantics> <mrow> <mi>m</mi><msqrt> <mrow> <mfrac> <mi>g</mi> <mi>R</mi> </mfrac> </mrow> </msqrt> </mrow> <annotation encoding=\"MathType-MTEF\">MathType@MTEF@5@5@@3951@</annotation> </semantics> </math>",
        "image": null
      },
      {
        "label": "K = gR",
        "image": null
      }
    ],
    "answer": "K = mgR"
  },
